<h4><a id="DeterminateSentence">Determinate Sentence</a></h4>
<p>A sentence of confinement to the New York State Department of Correctional Services for a fixed period that is specified by statute.  </p>

<h4><a id="PostReleaseSupervision">Post-Release Supervision</a> </h4>
<p>A period of community supervision by the New York State Division of Parole with conditions set by the Board of Parole. This period of supervision is imposed after most releases from the New York State Department of Correctional Services. </p>

<h4><a id="CASAT">CASAT</a></h4>
<p>Stands for “Comprehensive Alcohol and Substance Abuse Treatment.” Program developed in response to the growing number of inmates with alcohol and substance abuse problems. In CASAT inmates are treated during their incarceration by contractors in separate facilities while they are reintegrated into the community.</p>

<h4><a id="DefiniteSentence"></a>Definite Sentence</h4>
<p>A sentence of confinement to a local correctional facility for a term of one year or less.</p>

<h4><a id="IntermittentImprisonment"></a>Intermittent Imprisonment</h4>
<p>A sentence of altering periods of release and confinement, during which a defendant is released for the purposes of employment during the week, and allowed to serve the sentence of confinement during the weekend. </p>

<h4><a id="SupervisedParole"></a>Parole Supervision</h4>
<p>An indeterminate sentence of imprisonment which, after the court makes the requisite findings of fact, may be imposed upon an eligible defendant, wherein defendant is immediately taken from a maximum of 10 days at a specified department of corrections reception center, and delivered for 90 days at a drug treatment campus, after which defendant will be released therefrom.</p>

<h4><a id="Probation"></a>Probation</h4>
<p>A sentence of community supervision with conditions set by the court at the time of sentence. </p>

<h4><a id="InterimProbationSupervision"></a>Interim Probation Supervision</h4>
<p>A pre-sentencing order where the court adjourns sentencing for a period not to exceed one year, and places the defendant under the supervision of probation with a series of conditions. </p>

<h4><a id="ConditionalDischarge"></a>Conditional Discharge</h4>
<p>A sentence of the court that requires the completion of specified conditions that must be completed within a period that may be up to three years for a felony and one year for a misdemeanor. </p>

<h4><a id="UnconditionalDischarge"></a>Unconditional Discharge</h4>
<p>A sentence of the court resulting in a final judgment of conviction without imprisonment, fine, probation supervision or any other terms or conditions .</p>

<h4><a id="shock"></a>SHOCK</h4>
<p>A program  in which inmates who are less than 50 years in  age and have no prior state prison time, may be selected serve a period of six months in a shock incarceration facility,  which  provides them with  rigorous  physical  activity, intensive  regimentation, discipline, and rehabilitation therapy and programming. Upon successful completion of the six month period of shock incarceration the offender is released to serve the remainder of his sentence under the supervision of the New York State Division of Parole with conditions set by the New York State Board of Parole. </p>

<h4><a id="JudicialDiversion"></a>Judicial Diversion</h4>
<p>Program intended to provide an alternative track for specially identified cases. This program involves the placement of a defendant in a 6 to 12 month diversion, with specific conditions that are determined on a case-by-case basis. Individuals that successfully complete the Judicial Diversion Program are then given special consideration that may result in a reduction or dismissal of their charges .</p>

<h4><a id="SplitSentence"></a>Split Sentence</h4>
<p>A sentence in which the first part of the sentence is served in local imprisonment and the second part is served under community probation supervision.</p>
